The '''streaky-breasted spiderhunter''' ('''''Arachnothera affinis''''') is a species of bird in the family [[Nectariniidae]].
It is found in [[Java]] and [[Bali]].  Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s. It is sometimes considered conspecific with the [[grey-breasted spiderhunter]].

